Description:
    Creates a new basic chrome extension structure.

Example:
    yo chromeExtension

    This will create:
        popup.html: popup.html will be rendered inside the popup window that's created in response to a user's click on the browser action.
        manifest.json: The manifest is nothing more than a JSON-formatted table of contents, containing properties like your extension's name and description, its version number, and so on.
        package.json: Development packages installed by npm.

        css/: Your css files.
        js/: Your javascript files.
